      • build

        public TransactionList build(@Nullable
                             Client client)
                      throws LocalValidationException
        Description copied from class: TransactionBuilder
        Construct the final, immutable transaction.

        If client is not null, then some defaults are added if they are not otherwise set:

        • TransactionBuilder.setNodeAccountId(AccountId), if not manually set, is set with a random node chosen from the set that Client was constructed with
        • TransactionBuilder.setMaxTransactionFee(Hbar), if not manually set, is set with the value of Client.getMaxTransactionFee()
        • TransactionBuilder.setTransactionId(TransactionId) is set by calling TransactionId(AccountId) with the operator account if perviously set by Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey).
        • Transaction.sign(PrivateKey) is called with the operator private key if also previously set by Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey) (but only if TransactionBuilder.setTransactionId(TransactionId) was not called with a different account ID in the transaction ID).
        The last two items imply that the operator account set with Client.setOperator(AccountId, PrivateKey) will be paying the fee for this transaction if not otherwise specified.
        Specified by:
        build in class TransactionBuilder<TransactionId,TransactionList,ConsensusMessageSubmitTransaction>
        Parameters:
        client - the client to retrieve defaults from.
        Returns:
        the built Transaction, signed by the operator key in the client if applicable.
        Throws:
        LocalValidationException - if the transaction fails local sanity checks.
